│[1m                          [0m│ The validation system itself wasn’t pointed at this issue, but the seed could be improved │
│[1m                          [0m│ by enabling parameter sharing to be more parameter-efficient and symmetry-friendly.       │
│[1m                          [0m│                                                                                           │
│[1m                          [0m│ Fix: Modify the ANSATZ_SPEC within the EVOLVE-BLOCK so that all 9 RY gates share a single │
│[1m                          [0m│ parameter name (ry_shared) within a block, while keeping rz_pre and rz_post gates and the │
│[1m                          [0m│ CZ connections unchanged. This preserves the interface and training loop, but reduces the │
│[1m                          [0m│ per-block parameter count from 27 to 19, improving efficiency and potentially reducing    │
│[1m                          [0m│ the training gap. All other gates remain the same and are unchanged to maintain the task  │
│[1m                          [0m│ setup.                                                                                    │
