│[1m [0m[1mpatch_description       [0m[1m [0m│ Root cause: The dynamic construction of ANSATZ_SPEC in the EVOLVE-BLOCK (using Python     │
│[1m                          [0m│ loops) can introduce subtle inconsistencies between the parameter-key ordering and how    │
│[1m                          [0m│ parameters are mapped during apply_ansatz_block, which may trigger SPEC_ERRORS during     │
│[1m                          [0m│ validation and cause the evaluation to fail. To guarantee deterministic, valid indexing   │
│[1m                          [0m│ and adjacency, switch to a fixed, explicit ANSATZ_SPEC that mirrors the intended seed     │
│[1m                          [0m│ configuration (per-qubit RY, per-qubit pre-CZ RZ, fixed CZ edges, per-qubit post-CZ RZ).  │
│[1m                          [0m│ This ensures the validator sees a well-formed spec with a known parameter ordering and    │
│[1m                          [0m│ valid gate placements.                                                                    │
