│[1m [0m[1mpatch_description       [0m[1m [0m│ The bug is in the EVOLVE-BLOCK section. The ANSATZ_SPEC is currently set to a             │
│[1m                          [0m│ documentation string instead of a valid list of gate dictionaries:                        │
│[1m                          [0m│                                                                                           │
│[1m                          [0m│ ```python                                                                                 │
│[1m                          [0m│ # EVOLVE-BLOCK-START                                                                      │
│[1m                          [0m│ - Single-qubit parametrized gates:                                                        │
│[1m                          [0m│   {"gate": "RX"|"RY"|"RZ", "wire": int 0..8, "param": "name"}                             │
│[1m                          [0m│ # EVOLVE-BLOCK-END                                                                        │
│[1m                          [0m│ ```                                                                                       │
│[1m                          [0m│                                                                                           │
│[1m                          [0m│ This is invalid Python and causes `validate_ansatz_spec()` to fail because ANSATZ_SPEC is │
│[1m                          [0m│ not a list of dictionaries. The validation function checks `if not isinstance(spec, list) │
│[1m                          [0m│ or not spec:` and returns an error.                                                       │
│[1m                          [0m│                                                                                           │
│[1m                          [0m│ The fix is to replace this placeholder documentation with a valid ANSATZ_SPEC list. I'm   │
│[1m                          [0m│ restoring the seed ansatz (Pauli-2 style) which is a proven working baseline: RY and RZ   │
│[1m                          [0m│ on every qubit, CZ on each adjacent grid edge, then RZ on every qubit again.              │
